This paper is about remote sensing image classification using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of crowd-source data for annotation, which involves machine learning techniques for data processing and analysis, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of transfer learning and generalization ability of the models, which are topics covered in the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the classification of land use, which is related to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential practical applications of the proposed benchmark, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
